<objective>
  Determine the maximum safe context window and best optimization configuration for
  Qwen3-14B + speculative decoding (Qwen3-0.6B draft) on Intel Arc 140V (Xe2) GPU
  with ~16 GB shared LPDDR5X memory.

  The current MAX_OUTPUT_TOKENS=4,096 cap was set based on an obsolete study
  (P5-FEASIBILITY-001) that analyzed Qwen2.5-1.5B on NPU — a model and device no
  longer in the architecture (ADR-011 moved all LLM inference to GPU, NPU retired).
  
  This milestone produces the empirical data required for the Lead Architect to set
  a new context window cap via a future ADR amendment. No cap changes are made in
  this milestone.
</objective>

<prior_art_summary>
  <p5_005a_results>
    P5-005a (commit e6a64c4) ran 18 test configurations across prompt bands [128, 256, 512, 1024, 2048, 3072, 4096].
    Key findings relevant to P5-005b:

    BEST 14B CONFIG — T-09 (14B + 0.6B draft GPU, runtime_properties={}, num_assistant_tokens=5):
      Band 128:  13.08 tps, TTFT 415ms, RSS 9296 MB
      Band 256:  15.82 tps, TTFT 415ms, RSS 9340 MB
      Band 512:  13.77 tps, TTFT 400ms, RSS 9365 MB
      Band 1024: 13.24 tps, TTFT 396ms, RSS 9571 MB
      Band 2048:  8.99 tps, TTFT 459ms, RSS 9731 MB
      Band 3072: 10.48 tps, TTFT 498ms, RSS 9889 MB
      Band 4096:  9.58 tps, TTFT 529ms, RSS 10057 MB
      Speedup vs baseline: 3.18x at band 512

    14B BASELINE — T-01 (no draft, no optimizations):
      Band 512:  4.33 tps, TTFT 463ms, RSS 9100 MB
      Band 4096: 3.36 tps, TTFT 686ms, RSS 9539 MB

    CRITICAL FINDINGS FROM P5-005a AUDIT:
    1. INT8 KV cache (KV_CACHE_PRECISION=u8) HURTS decode TPS on Arc 140V — do NOT use.
    2. XAttention (GPU_ENABLE_SDPA_OPTIMIZATION) was NEVER tested without INT8 KV — T-03
       combined both; INT8 contaminated the measurement. Must be isolated.
    3. Speculative decoding tests (T-09..T-12) ran with runtime_properties={} — never
       combined with XAttention. This is the biggest untested combination.
    4. Only num_assistant_tokens=5 was tested — no sweep performed.
    5. No data exists beyond 4,096 tokens — the entire extended-context decision space is unmapped.
    6. T-03/T-04 were effectively identical configs due to prefix_cache_api_present=False.
  </p5_005a_results>

  <kv_cache_memory_math>
    Qwen3-14B architecture (from models/qwen3-14b/openvino-int4-gpu/config.json):
      num_hidden_layers=40, num_key_value_heads=8, head_dim=128, max_position_embeddings=40960

    Qwen3-0.6B architecture (from models/qwen3-0.6b/openvino-int4-gpu/config.json):
      num_hidden_layers=28, num_key_value_heads=8, head_dim=128

    Theoretical KV bytes/token (FP16):
      14B: 2 * 8 * 128 * 2 * 40 = 163,840 bytes/token (160 KiB/token)
      0.6B: 2 * 8 * 128 * 2 * 28 = 114,688 bytes/token (112 KiB/token)
      Combined ceiling: 272 KiB/token

    Empirical KV growth from T-09: RSS grew 761 MB over 3,968 tokens ≈ 196 KiB/token observed.

    Memory projections (14B + 0.6B draft, base model load ~9,262 MB):
      Context  4,096: Total ~10,350 MB theoretical / ~10,046 MB empirical   (MEASURED ✓)
      Context  8,192: Total ~11,438 MB theoretical / ~10,830 MB empirical   (within budget)
      Context 12,288: Total ~12,526 MB theoretical / ~11,614 MB empirical   (comfortable)
      Context 16,384: Total ~13,614 MB theoretical / ~12,398 MB empirical   (feasible)
      Context 20,480: Total ~14,702 MB theoretical / ~13,182 MB empirical   (tight)
      Context 24,576: Total ~15,790 MB theoretical / ~13,966 MB empirical   (ceiling zone)
      Context 32,768: Total ~17,966 MB theoretical / ~15,534 MB empirical   (OOM expected)

    GPU shared memory ceiling: ~16 GB (dynamic allocation from 32 GB LPDDR5X system RAM).
  </kv_cache_memory_math>

  <p5_001_obsolescence>
    The original DO-NOT-EXPAND decision (docs/FEASIBILITY_CONTEXT_WINDOW.md) was based on:
    1. NPU latency scaling concerns — no longer applicable (ADR-011: GPU only)
    2. 1,024 MB Orchestrator memory budget — was for Qwen2.5-1.5B in system RAM; GPU has ~16 GB
    3. Qwen2.5-1.5B architecture (2 KV heads, 28 layers) — replaced by Qwen3-14B (8 KV heads, 40 layers)
    All three premises are invalidated. A new empirical study is required.
  </p5_001_obsolescence>
</prior_art_summary>

